  <article id="section-persistent-search">
    <h2 class="app-article-headline hca-typography--headline">Persistent Search</h2>
    <section class="app-section">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-5">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">The search text field is presented inside of an inset search box, ready to receive focus.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">When in focus, the search field can expand to show historical search suggestions, most frequent searches or suggested results based on user input. If needed, the onscreen keyboard will also appear.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Choosing any of the suggestions submits the search.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">As the user enters a query, the search suggestions shift to auto-completion. As the user types, the suggestions are filtered and sorted. Choosing a suggestion or pressing the return key submits the search.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">The close (X) icon in the search box clears the query and closes the search.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">When displaying submitted search results, the search box remains visible, but is not focused by default. The onscreen keyboard is dismissed so more results can be shown.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Search results are usually displayed as a list, but, on large devices, may be formatted as cards to accommodate different types of results and to offer richer result experiences.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
